Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Content:
From the response, can you please help me understand something? I'm rewriting part of your Mastering CC stuff.

I want to be able to show how a utxo has no vouts yet, but the response that I'm getting here does have vouts.

Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Bryan_Beus#6442
Content: We talk in the content about how a utxo has a vin, and the future transaction that spends it consumes its vouts...

Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Content: Oh!

Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Content: Wait, I think maybe I get it.

Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Content: So, a utxo has vouts, but there are no vins that match it in the chain, is that right?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: to be able to spent a utxo, it needs to start as a vout

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: when you spend it, it is used as a vin

Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Content:
That is to say, when a user spends a utxo, the data structure of the utxo in the database does not change. Rather, there is a new transaction created that has vins that match the vouts of the utxo. 

And this would explain why, for any given address, to find out the current value in that address, you must scan from the beginning of the chain?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it is indeed a bit confusing

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: yes, unless a chain has -addressindex functionality (or spentindex)

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the raw chain just has vins and vouts

Author: Bryan_Beus#6442
Content: Gotcha.

Content: Ahh, cool. Learned something new!
